info.title: FAA LAANC REST API Documentation [API Version 5]
info.description:
### **Introduction** The Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) is responsible for implementing authorization processes specific to operation of small unmanned aircraft systems (sUAS) – see 14 CFR Part 107.41, and Section 349, § 44809. From an Air Traffic (AT) perspective, authorization of unmanned aviation activity enables the provision of safe and efficient flight services to all aircraft in the National Airspace System (NAS). To meet the need for efficient authorization processes, the FAA created the Low Altitude Authorization and Notification Capability (LAANC). LAANC includes a partnership between the FAA and private UAS Service Suppliers (USSs). See the LAANC Concept of Operations document for more detail on the function and features of LAANC. #### **Purpose** This document presents the interface details for automated communication between USSs and the FAA’s LAANC infrastructure. It provides technical guidance for LAANC implementation and USSs that are provided access. The intended distribution of this API Specification is among USSs that have signed a LAANC Memorandum of Agreement (MOA) with the FAA. It is not intended for public distribution; note "For Official Use Only" designation. #### **Scope** Only the USS-FAA automated interfaces are described in this document. Other aspects of LAANC implementation and processes are not included. USSs and the FAA will have other non-automated interactions not described here (see "USS Performance Rules"). There are also technical interactions between the USS and FAA that are not described in this document; for example, the USS interface to the FAA ArcGIS system that provides map information. This document will be revised from time to time as LAANC interface details develop and change. #### **System Identification** LAANC consists of various roles, systems, and processes. The systems relevant to this API Specification are the FAA LAANC infrastructure ("LAANC Automation Platform", LAANC-AP) and the USS systems that connect to LAANC-AP. ### **Referenced Sources** * Federal Aviation Administration, Advisory Circular: 107-2, "Small Unmanned Aircraft Systems (sUAS)", 21 June 2016 * Federal Aviation Administration, "Integration of Unmanned Aircraft Systems into the National Airspace System, Concept of Operations v2.1", March 2020 * "Low Altitude Authorization and Notification Capability (LAANC) Concept of Operations", current version * LAANC USS Performance Rules * U.S. Government Publishing Office, Code of Federal Regulations, Title 14, 107 ("Small Unmanned Aircraft Systems") * FAA Modernization and Reform Act of 2012, Pub. L. 112-95 (Feb. 14, 2012) * FAA Extension, Safety, and Security Act of 2016, Pub. L. 114-190 (July 15, 2016) * FAA Reauthorization Act of 2018, Pub. L. 115-254, Section 349, § 44809 (Oct 5, 2018) * Federal Aviation Administration, Airman’s Information Manual (AIM), January 1, 2020 ### **LAANC Interface for Authorizations** #### **General Characteristics** The LAANC-AP interface for authorizations is designed according to REST (Representational State Transfer) principles and standard web technologies. Hypertext Transfer Protocol Secure (HTTPS) v1.1 is the underlying protocol used for all authorization messaging between USSs and LAANC-AP. Authentication is associated with messaging on this interface from USSs to LAANC-AP. See "Authentication" link at the top of the page to obtain the "LAANC Interface for USS Authentication" document. USSs must include authentication information in each call to the LAANC-AP API. Text fields received in LAANC API calls can be any valid Latin character specified here: [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Latin_script_in_Unicode](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Latin_script_in_Unicode). The only exception is, 'Safety Justification' which is limited to: Basic Latin, Latin-1 Supplement, and Latin Extended-A. Any Latin character outside of this range is rejected. #### **FAA LAANC REST API Documentation [Authorizations]** The interface described here is referred to as API version 5. #### **URI scheme** **BasePath:** /laanc

Appendix A: Acronyms | Acronym or Term | Description | | --------------- | ----------- | | A&N | Authorization and Notification | | AGL | Above Ground Level | | AIM | Airman’s Information Manual | | API | Application Programming Interface | | AT | Air Traffic | | ATC | Air Traffic Control | | ATM | Air Traffic Management | | ECC | Enterprise Control Center | | FAA | Federal Aviation Administration | | GeoJSON | Geographic JavaScript Object Notation | | GIS | Geographic Information System | | GMT | Greenwich Mean Time | | HTTPS | Hypertext Transfer Protocol Secure | | JSON | JavaScript Object Notation | | JWT | JSON Web Token | | LAANC | Low Altitude Authorization and Notification Capability | | MOA | Memorandum of Agreement | | NAS | National Airspace System | | PII | Personally Identifiable Information | | REST | Representational State Transfer | | RFC | Request for Comments | | RSA | Rivest-Shamir-Adleman (digital signing algorithm) | | SUA | Special Use Airspace | | sUAS | Small UAS | | TLS | Transport Layer Security | | UAS | Unmanned Aircraft System | | UASFM | UAS Facility Map | | URI | Uniform Resource Identifier | | USS | UAS Service Supplier | | UTM | UAS Traffic Management | | WGS84 | World Geodetic System 1984 |

Appendix B: USS-FAA LAANC Error Codes

Contact the FAA LAANC Program Office for the Appendix B: USS-FAA LAANC Error Codes.

post.description:
Call this method to store a Part 107 Auto Authorization. Input must be a valid GeoJSON Feature Collection and, once validation is passed, a Part 107 Auto Authorization will be stored.

Acceptable GeoJSON Geometry is a valid Point or Polygon with the proper corresponding coordinates. The coordinate reference system for all GeoJSON coordinates is a geographic coordinate reference system, using the World Geodetic System 1984 (WGS 84) [WGS84] datum, with longitude and latitude units of decimal degrees. Type must be "Feature" and must contain Properties with the operation information. A Polygon must be a valid closed polygon with no interior rings. Note: polygons may be clockwise or counterclockwise.

Validations will be conducted when this method is called. If a field is not valid, or within the automatically approved altitude threshold, an exception will be thrown, and the auto authorization will not be saved.

Call this method to acknowledge any Authorizations that were rescinded by AT.  Input must be an operation id that can identify the operation.  This method should be used by the USS for operators to acknowledge an operation that was rescinded by AT. The method can be called at any time after the authorization is rescinded.

Validations will be conducted when this method is called. If a field is not valid, an exception will be thrown, and the acknowledgement will not be completed.

post.description:
Call this method to indicate the termination of an operation was closed by the operator after the authorized operation has started, but prior to the submitted end time. Input must be an operation id that can identify the operation. If the call to this endpoint is successfully processed: 1) counts for count107Close and count44809Close should be incremented accordingly; and 2) the operation status is considered "Complete". This method can only be called after the start time of the operation, otherwise it returns an error.

Validations will be conducted when this method is called. If a field is not valid, an exception will be thrown, and the close will not be completed.

post.description:
Call this method to indicate any Authorization record that has been deleted by the user. Input must be an operation id that can identify the request for operation. This method should be used by the USS for operator-initiated deletion requests. Calling this method will cause the data to be marked as deleted on the FAA-side and will be omitted from type (i.e., 107 and 44809) counts in the O&M statistics. Calling the Delete Endpoint will impact the Operational Statistics by incrementing the countLaancCallSuccess; similar to the update endpoint calls, but will not increase/decrease the other counts.

Validations will be conducted when this method is called. If a field is not valid, an exception will be thrown, and the deletion will not be completed. Operations can only be deleted when they have reached a terminal state (complete, never-authorized, or de-authorized). USS may need to coordinate with the operator to get the operations to a terminal state. If the operation state is not valid, an exception will be thrown, and the deletion will not be completed.

Call this method to trigger the Notify response of the USS Webhook API. Input must be an operation id with a prefix of "NOOP".  This method should be used by the USS to test if the webhook functionality is behaving correctly in any environment, notably in the Production Environment.

Validations will be conducted when this method is called. If a field is not valid, an exception will be thrown, and the processing will not be completed.

Calling this method will return a 200 HTTP status code response of OK with no Body.

get.description: Call this end point to retrieve all the submissions that are active/open (i.e., authorized or pending). Note that completed, pending, and never-authorized operations are not listed. By default, this endpoint lists 100 reference codes (active/open only) and their state, along with a "next_page_key" parameter. The list will be ordered according to the order in which the original operations submissions were received. The "next_page_key" is a key that should be used in the path of the following request to retrieve the next page results. Calls that include the "next_page_key" parameter will be limited to those results gathered in the original call to this endpoint – underlying data changes since the time of the original (page 1) call will not be included in subsequent "next page" calls. If the original results are limited to a single page, the "next_page_key" is omitted.  Number of reference codes returned can be limited by using the "limit" parameter in the path, up to a max of 500.

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: Limits the number of operations returned per page in the response. (Default = 100, max = 500)

parameters.name: next_page_key
parameters.description: Instructs the endpoint to return the next page of results.  The key is derived from the previous page response metadata.

200.description: OK (Note: when no open operations exist, the response will return a status 200 OK code with no Body.)

get.description: Call this end point to retrieve the operational statistics of operations between the datetime range passed and verify that the statistics match sufficiently – and thereby ensure proper operations on both sides. **How Operations are Filtered** Operation start datetimes and operation end datetimes of authorizations, not authorization submission datetimes, are used to return the statistics for the defined time span in the call. If the duration of an operation touches the filter criteria, it is returned. The image below visually represents this concept. With time represented horizontally, each yellow highlighted bar represents an operation and its duration. The first vertical dashed line represents the filter start datetime and the second dash represents the filter end datetime. In the below examples, all the highlighted operations would be returned by the endpoint.

parameters.name: datetimeStart
parameters.description: Start date and time of the operations in ISO format.

parameters.name: datetimeEnd
parameters.description: End date and time of the operations in ISO format.

parameters.name: facility
parameters.description: Three/Four char facility ID. If none provided all the facilities statistics are returned. (more than one facility accepted when comma separated)

get.description:
Call this endpoint to retrieve the FAA system status and the versions that are in use (software versions, data model versions, critical dataset versions, etc.). Codes for "internal use" are diagnostic identifiers that have significance to some FAA recipients (such as the Enterprise Control Center (ECC) or system monitoring groups). Internal use codes will not generally be published. Dataset values are the Authoritative Source for that service. Last edit dates are populated from the editingInfo attribute contained in JSON metadata for the Data Source link. | Information Type | Authoritative Source (Permanent Link) | | ---------------- | ------------------------------------- | | UAS Facility Maps (UASFMs) | https://udds-faa.opendata.arcgis.com/datasets/ee469d2965014d978d1973c440119152_0 | | Full-Time National Security UAS Flight Restrictions (NSUFRs) | https://udds-faa.opendata.arcgis.com/datasets/0270b9d8a5d34217856cc03aaf833309_0 | | Part-Time National Security UAS Flight Restrictions (NSUFRs) | https://udds-faa.opendata.arcgis.com/datasets/3a4a808aec634e4e8e4b0ee0d5366da6_0 | | Class Airspace | https://adds-faa.opendata.arcgis.com/datasets/c6a62360338e408cb1512366ad61559e_0 | | Airports | https://adds-faa.opendata.arcgis.com/datasets/e747ab91a11045e8b3f8a3efd093d3b5_0 | | Stadiums | https://adds-faa.opendata.arcgis.com/datasets/67af16061c014365ae9218c489a321be_0 | | Washington D.C. FRZ | https://adds-faa.opendata.arcgis.com/datasets/67885972e4e940b2aa6d74024901c561_0 | | Special User Airspace | https://adds-faa.opendata.arcgis.com/datasets/dd0d1b726e504137ab3c41b21835d05b_0 | | Airspace Schedule | https://adds-faa.opendata.arcgis.com/datasets/811863566da44acf91cb42f82ad0ac99_0 |
**How to Populate Authoritative Source Data** 1. Go to the permanent link. 2. Airspace example: https://adds-faa.opendata.arcgis.com/datasets/c6a62360338e408cb1512366ad61559e_0 3. Go to the "Data Source" link, specifying the JSON version. Example (note "?f=pjson" at the end): https://services6.arcgis.com/ssFJjBXIUyZDrSYZ/arcgis/rest/services/Class_Airspace/FeatureServer/0?f=pjson 4. Extract the "lastEditDate" from the "editingInfo" attribute. Example: "editingInfo": {"lastEditDate": 1570714332975} 5. (Optional) Convert the date/timestamp from epoch milliseconds format to UTC. Example: 1570714332975 = October 10, 2019 13:32:12.975 6. Convert to ISO format (trim the milliseconds)

get.description:
Each call made to USS endpoints will include a LAANC generated and signed JWT.  The JWT will be included in the header under "Authorization" key. The LAANC system uses the type "FAALAANC", for example:

Authorization: FAALAANC <JWT>

The JWT will contain 3 parts as defined in RFC 7519 (https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7519), the header, payload, and signature.  The header contains the signing algorithm and a key ID.  The payload contains the token expiration timestamp.

In order to verify the authenticity of each request, the USS application will use the LAANC public key matching the provided key ID (36-character UUID/GUID) to validate the signature.  The USS must retrieve the public key from the LAANC server; the key should be cached so that future JWTs referencing the same key ID may be validated without additional roundtrips to the LAANC system.  If the token has not expired and the signature is valid, then the request should be granted. If the input key ID is not found, a 404 response will be returned.

parameters.name: kid
parameters.description: kid used to retrieve associated public key.  (Format: required=xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx)

The type of geometry object. (Value: Feature)

code.description: Error code associated with the error.

field.description: The name of the field failing validation.

message.description: A message to explain why this field failed validation.

LaancErrorDTO.description: Note: More information about the error(s) is returned in the Response. See Appendix B: USS-FAA LAANC Error Codes for additional information on error responses.

operation.description: The unique identifier for the operation.

state.description: Status of the operation. (Values: "Authorized" - Approved authorization that has not yet finished, "Pending" - Active request has not yet been approved or denied, "Rescinded_Awaiting" - authorization rescinded and acknowledgement needed from operator)

submissionType.description: The operation submission type, Auto approved or further coordination. (Values: "AA", "FC")

airspaceClassCodes.description: The list of Airspace Class Codes. Allowed values: "B", "C", "D", "E"

facility.description: The unique identifier for the facility. (Size: min=3, max=4)

facilityMaps.description: The list of facility maps that the operation will intersect. Each element must include the globalId and lastEditDate for that facility map grid.

operationDuration.description: The length of time in minutes of the operation. The duration must be between 1 and 720 minutes.

operationID.description: The unique identifier for the operation. (Size: required=9)

operationMaxAltitude.description: The maximum operation altitude above ground level (AGL) in feet. (value: min=1, max=400)

operationRadius.description: For Points, the distance in nautical miles of the operation from the provided latitude and longitude point. For Polygons, no value can be specified. (Size: min=1 char, max=10 chars; Value: max linear extent =10nmi; Format: floating point number)

operationStartDateTime.description: The start date and time of the operation. The start date and time must be in the future but cannot be more than 90 days in the future. (Format: required= yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ ). Time Zone is UTC

pocFirstName.description: The point of contact's first name. (Size: max=60 characters)

pocLastName.description: The point of contact's last name. (Size: max=60 characters)

pocPhoneNumber.description: The point of contact’s phone number. (Size: min=2, max=15)

registrationNumbers.description: The list of registration numbers for the sUASs that will be operated during the operation. (Size: min=1, max=13)

type.description: The type of geometry object. (Value: Feature)

ackRescindDateTime.description:
Time at which the operation was acknowledged, if acknowledged. (Values: Time in format required=yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ  or null)

Note: "ackRescindDateTime" is required when there is a corresponding time value. When the value is null "ackRescindDateTime" may be omitted from the message.

approvalDateTime.description:
Time at which the operation was approved, if approved. (Values: Time in format required=yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ  or null)

Note: "approvalDateTime" is required when there is a corresponding time value. When the value is null "approvalDateTime" may be omitted from the message.

cancelDateTime.description:
Time at which the operation was cancelled, if cancelled. (Values: Time in format required=yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ  or null)

Note: "cancelDateTime" is required when there is a corresponding time value. When the value is null "cancelDateTime" may be omitted from the message.

Valid cancellation types include operator, automatic, or invalid. Attributes with a null value may be omitted but are included in this example for completeness.

changeDateTime.description:
Time at which the operation was changed/updated, if applicable. (Values: Time in format required=yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ  or null)

Note: "changeDateTime" is required when there is a corresponding time value. When the value is null "changeDateTime" may be omitted from the message.

closeDateTime.description:
Time at which the operation was closed, if closed. (Values: Time in format required=yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ  or null)

Note: "closeDateTime" is required when there is a corresponding time value. When the value is null "closeDateTime" may be omitted from the message.

denialDateTime.description:
Time at which the operation was denied, if denied. (Values: Time in format required=yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ  or null)

Note: "denialDateTime" is required when there is a corresponding time value. When the value is null "denialDateTime" may be omitted from the message.

rescindDateTime.description:
Time at which the operation was rescinded, if applicable. (Values: Time in format required=yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ  or null)

Note: "rescindDateTime" is required when there is a corresponding time value. When the value is null "rescindDateTime" may be omitted from the message.

status.description:
Status of the operation. (Values: 
1.	"Authorized" – approved authorization that has not been Completed or De-Authorized
2.	 "Complete" – approved authorization that has finished at its submitted end time, or by an operator action indicating the authorization is closed.
Note: Includes authorizations detected as invalid that have not been invalid cancelled by the operator, but have reached its submitted end time.
3.	"Pending" – active authorization request that has not yet been approved or denied.
4.	 "Never Authorized" – pending authorization request that was denied, expired, or cancelled (i.e., automatic invalid, or operator).
5.	"De-Authorized" – authorization was cancelled (i.e., operator, invalid), or rescinded.

Notes:
(1) Operator cancel and invalid cancel can only occur prior to the submitted start time.
(2) Rescind acknowledgement can occur any time after the authorization is rescinded, but prior to the submitted end time.
(3) Includes rescinded authorizations not acknowledged by the submitted end time.
6. "Rescinded_Awaiting" – authorization rescinded and awaiting operator acknowledgement.

count107AaSubmitted.description: Count of 107/autoauthorization API calls for operations starting in the given time window range which is provided as API call input parameters.

count107Cancelled.description: Count of cancelOperation API calls for 107 operations that have a start time within the given time window range which is provided as API call input parameters. This count is based solely on the operation start date/time and not the cancellation date/time.

count107Close.description: Count of closeOperation API calls for 107 operations that have a start time within the given time window range which is provided as API call input parameters. This count is based solely on the operation start date/time and not the closure date/time.

count107FcApproved.description: The count of approved 107 FC operations that have an operation start time within the time window range.  This count is based solely on the operation start date/time and not the approval date/time.

count107FcDenied.description: The count of denied 107 FC operations that have an operation start time within the time window range.  This count is based solely on the operation start date/time and not the denial date/time.

count107FcExpired.description:
Count of expired events for 107 operations that have a start time within the given time window range.

__Note: This count is for LAANC-AP only. Count must be 0 to be compliant with USS Performance Rules.__

count107FcSubmitted.description: Count of 107/requestauthorization API calls for 107 operations that have a start time within the given time window range which is provided as API call input parameters.

count107InvalidCancel.description: Count of invalidcancelOperation API calls for 107 operations that have a start time within the given time window range which is provided as API call input parameters. This count is based solely on the operation start date/time and not the cancellation date/time.

count107RescindAck.description: Count of ackRescindedOperation API calls for 107 operations that have a start time within the given time window range which is provided as API call input parameters. This count is based solely on the operation start date/time and not the rescind acknowledgement date/time.

count107Rescinded.description: The count of rescinded 107 operations that have an operation start time within the time window range.  This count is based solely on the operation start date/time and not the rescission date/time.

count44809AaSubmitted.description: Count of 44809/autoauthorization API calls for 44809 operations that have a start time within the given time window range which is provided as API call input parameters.

count44809Cancelled.description: Count of cancelOperation API calls for 44809 operations that have a start time within the given time window range which is provided as API call input parameters. This count is based solely on the operation start date/time and not the cancellation date/time.

count44809Close.description: Count of closeOperation API calls for 44809 operations that have a start time within the given time window range which is provided as API call input parameters. This count is based solely on the operation start date/time and not the closure date/time.

count44809InvalidCancel.description: Count of invalidcancelOperation API calls for 44809 operations that have a start time within the given time window range which is provided as API call input parameters. This count is based solely on the operation start date/time and not the cancellation date/time.

count44809RescindAck.description: Count of ackRescindedOperation API calls for 44809 operations that have a start time within the given time window range which is provided as API call input parameters. This count is based solely on the operation start date/time and not the rescind acknowledgement date/time.

count44809Rescinded.description: Count of rescinded 44809 operations that have a start time within the given time window range. This count is based solely on the operation start date/time and not the rescission date/time.

countAutoCancelled.description: Count of autocancelOperation API calls for 107 operations that have a start time within the given time window range which is provided as API call input parameters. This count is based solely on the operation start date/time and not the cancellation date/time.

Count of successful API calls from the USS to LAANC
(countLaancCallSuccess=
count107OperationsSubmitted +

count107Close +

count44809InvalidCancel +

update calls to the Auto Authorization Update endpoints + calls to the Delete endpoint)
